Careers at UHS


Notification of recruiting scam using the UHS name:
It has been brought to our attention that a handful of cases have occurred around the country where scammers using the UHS name have attempted to lure unsuspecting job seekers into an arrangement whereby they would be asked to send money in exchange for a job with the company. This is a scam targeting job seekers and the individuals involved are not representatives of UHS.
If you are the victim of such a scam, we ask that you:

Notify the UHS Compliance Department at 1-800-852-3449
Notify local law enforcement authorities, the recruiting website and Google, being certain to include the email address of those who you were corresponding with
If you receive any checks DO NOT cash them. Instead, contact the Bank and inform them that you believe that you have received a fraudulent check and want to report it


Lead. Inspire. Succeed.
If you want to work for a company where you can build the career of your dreams, UHS may be the place for you.
If you are looking for a place where you can build the career of your dreams, UHS may be the place for you. At UHS, we're looking for exceptional people who share our vision and values, who share our focus on hard work, enthusiasm, teamwork, loyalty, trust and cooperation. We've embraced these traits and built a team of employees who consistently work to achieve the highest level of service excellence.
People are our most valuable resource at UHS as we are committed to providing high quality acute care and behavioral health services to residents of the communities we serve. We are equally committed to offering our employees unlimited opportunity in an environment that encourages professional development.
Opportunity to Grow
We know that providing a professional working environment and an opportunity to grow is a key to attracting and retaining talented, motivated employees. That's why we provide encouragement and support to employees who want to expand their knowledge and increase their proficiency through continuing education and job-related training. 
Service Excellence Drives UHS
Every UHS employee takes part in our Service Excellence program, and are guided by three standards:

Treat everyone as a guest.
Demonstrate professionalism and excellence in the things I do.
Practice teamwork.

These standards help ensure that the staff at all UHS acute care hospitals and behavioral health facilities deliver high quality care to every patient.
Education and Career Planning
The Behavioral Health Division of UHS recently added the Psychiatry Residency & Fellowship Education and Career Planning Program. This unique, complimentary program offers exclusive educational opportunities to residents and fellows by assisting them in navigating where business and medicine intertwine.
Learn more about the program (PDF) >
